## 4. Order of spans

As indicated above, the relation and schema definitions do not constrain the order of spans in the text. Ordering seems to be under the independent control of the writer . However, strong tendencies (canonical orders) have been observed:

**Table 2. Canonical orders of spans for some relations** 

| Satellite before Nucleus | Nucleus before Satellite |
| --- | --- |
| Antithesis | Elaboration |
| Background | Enablement |
| Concessive | Evidence |
| Conditional | Purpose |
| Justify | Restatement |
| Solutionhood |  |

We have observed that if a natural text is rewritten to convert the instances of non-canonical span order to canonical order, it seldom reduces text quality and often improves it.

